         <div type="transcription">
            <p><milestone unit="passage" n="9.11c-9.18c"/>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>postän</w><w>no</w><w>räs<supplied>kare</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>buddhyate</w><pc>•</pc><w>ya<supplied>maskemane</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>pu</supplied>warsa</w><w><gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>e</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b4"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>kṣīra</supplied>m</w><w>iv<supplied>a</supplied></w><w><supplied>m</supplied>u<supplied>rcchati</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b5"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>i</supplied>vānalaḥ</w><w>s<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>e</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b6"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>sāṃparāye</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] later, however, (it becomes) bitter</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] (doing [bad deeds], a fool does not) recognise it [TB] doing [bad deeds], (a fool does not recognise it)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] (he is tormented as if burnt) by fire</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] [does not] (suddenly) curdle like milk</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] like fire (covered with ashes)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] (but) in the other world (one knows)</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels"><bibl><title corresp="ref:bernhard1965"/><citedRange>173-175</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:chakravarti1930"/><citedRange>103-107</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:hahn2007"/><citedRange>40-41</citedRange></bibl></note><note type="remarks">The upper margin of the recto (lower of the verso) is preserved. Lines a1-3 cover the 6 half pādas 9.11c-12d, lines b4-6 the 6 half pādas 9.17b-18c: the 17 half pādas in between will have covered three lines on each side and the total number of lines must have been 6.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment">Uv.9.11c <hi>paścāt tu kaṭukaṃ bhavati</hi></note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">Uv.9.12b <hi>kurvaṃ bālo na budhyate</hi></note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment">Uv.9.12d <hi>hy agnidagdhaiva tapyate</hi></note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment">Uv.9.17b <hi>sadyaḥ kṣīram iva mūrchati</hi>, var. lect. <hi>murcchati</hi> (<bibl><title corresp="ref:bernhard1965"/><citedRange>175</citedRange></bibl>).</note><note corresp="#b5" type="philcomment">Uv.9.17d <hi>bhasmācchanna ivānalaḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#b6" type="philcomment">Uv.9.18c <hi>sāmparāye tu jānāti</hi></note></p>
         </div>
